The paper focuses on decentralized distributed deep learning systems and achieving differential privacy, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed algorithm also involves a novel topology and trade-off analysis, which could fall under distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of differential privacy models and analysis suggests information theory (cs.IT) as another possible sub-category.
